00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:53,783
HOLY SMOKE!
WHAT THE FUCK?

238
00:10:53,827 --> 00:10:55,176
SORRY!

239
00:10:55,219 --> 00:10:57,831
♪ LORD, IN MY TIME
OF DYING ♪

240
00:10:57,874 --> 00:11:00,224
♪ DON'T WANT NOBODY
TO CRY... ♪

241
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:02,139
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

242
00:11:02,183 --> 00:11:04,098
IT'S LOWERDECK,
FROM "LOWERDECK"--

243
00:11:04,141 --> 00:11:05,752
"IN ALL HIS GLORY."

244
00:11:05,795 --> 00:11:07,014
OH, YOU'RE A FAN?

245
00:11:07,057 --> 00:11:08,929
OH, I'M A FAN.
I'M A BIG FAN.

246
00:11:11,279 --> 00:11:12,802
OH, MISTY, PLEASE DON'T.

247
00:11:12,846 --> 00:11:14,195
DO YOU HAVE ANY?

248
00:11:14,238 --> 00:11:16,501
I, UH... NO.

249
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:19,156
MILLIE, UM, I WAS
WONDERING IF YOU COULD--

250
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:22,943
EXCUSE ME.

251
00:11:25,206 --> 00:11:26,686
ARE YOU WATCHING
TONIGHT?

252
00:11:26,729 --> 00:11:27,817
IT'S GOING TO BE
TOTALLY LIVE.

253
00:11:27,861 --> 00:11:29,036
I KNOW.

254
00:11:29,079 --> 00:11:30,472
I'M... GOING.

255
00:11:30,515 --> 00:11:31,734
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

256
00:11:31,778 --> 00:11:33,301
IT'S LIKE ONE OF THOSE
UNPLUGGED SESSIONS.

257
00:11:33,344 --> 00:11:34,215
NO ONE GETS IN.

258
00:11:35,564 --> 00:11:37,261
WELL, I GUESS I'M LUCKY.

259
00:11:37,305 --> 00:11:38,567
YOU'RE GOING TO BE
NEAR HIM,

260
00:11:38,610 --> 00:11:40,569
AND NOW I'M NEAR YOU.

261
00:11:40,612 --> 00:11:41,657
IT'S NO BIG DEAL,
REALLY. I--

262
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:42,745
OH!

263
00:11:42,789 --> 00:11:44,225
I, UH, UM--

264
00:11:48,011 --> 00:11:49,578
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

265
00:11:54,888 --> 00:11:56,498
I'M NOT A LESBIAN.

266
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:57,934
MILLIE,

267
00:11:57,978 --> 00:11:59,544
WE'VE ALL EXPERIMENTED.

268
00:11:59,588 --> 00:12:02,069
YOU--I HAVEN'T.

269
00:12:02,112 --> 00:12:04,114
IT'S NOT AS IF
I DIDN'T GO TO COLLEGE.

270
00:12:04,158 --> 00:12:06,769
WE'VE ALL PUT OUR BIG TOE
IN THAT WATER.

271
00:12:06,813 --> 00:12:07,727
I REALLY HAVEN'T.

272
00:12:12,253 --> 00:12:13,254
DELORES?

273
00:12:14,472 --> 00:12:15,343
[HITS KEY]

274
00:12:18,563 --> 00:12:20,957
YOU KNOW, WHEN YOU'RE YOUNG
LIKE YOU ARE, MILLIE,

275
00:12:21,001 --> 00:12:22,785
IT'S EASY.

276
00:12:22,829 --> 00:12:24,961
MAN, WOMAN, BOTTOM, TOP...

277
00:12:25,005 --> 00:12:27,007
SEX IS THIS BIG BUFFET,

278
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:30,140
AND YOU'RE JUST A FAT MAN
WITH A FORK,

279
00:12:30,184 --> 00:12:33,013
BUT AS YOU GET OLDER,
IT'S HARDER TO GET A FORK.

280
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:37,582
OKAY. THANKS.

281
00:12:37,626 --> 00:12:40,803
UM, I HAVE TO
LEAVE EARLY TODAY.

282
00:12:40,847 --> 00:12:42,587
ANOTHER DOCTOR'S APPOINTMENT?NO.

283
00:12:42,631 --> 00:12:44,285
A.A. MEETING?NO.

284
00:12:44,328 --> 00:12:46,200
WHAT, THEN?A ROCK CONCERT.

285
00:12:49,551 --> 00:12:51,379
ENJOY THE BUFFET, MILLIE.

286
00:12:51,422 --> 00:12:53,207
YEAH. OKAY, THANKS. BYE.

287
00:12:54,904 --> 00:12:56,906
[SIGHS]

288
00:12:56,950 --> 00:13:01,084
I'D LIKE TO GET A TICKET FOR
THE KYLE LOWERDECK CONCERT.

289
00:13:01,128 --> 00:13:02,651
[TICKET CLERK] <i>
SOLD OUT.</i>

290
00:13:04,566 --> 00:13:06,046
I HAVE $500?

291
00:13:06,089 --> 00:13:07,482
<i>OH, WELL,
IN THAT CASE...</i>

292
00:13:07,525 --> 00:13:08,570
<i>SOLD OUT.</i>

293
00:13:10,050 --> 00:13:12,443
ASSHOLE.

294
00:13:12,487 --> 00:13:14,706
AHEM. THAT SENSATION
YOU'RE FEELING...

295
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:16,926
WOULDN'T BE THE SENSATION
OF UTTER FAILURE, WOULD IT?

296
00:13:16,970 --> 00:13:18,188
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

297
00:13:18,232 --> 00:13:19,146
I'VE COME
TO SAVE YOUR ASS.

298
00:13:19,189 --> 00:13:20,625
LET'S GO TO THE CONCERT.

299
00:13:20,669 --> 00:13:21,670
YOU SCORED TICKETS?

300
00:13:21,713 --> 00:13:22,845
NO.

301
00:13:22,889 --> 00:13:24,151
THEN I'M SCREWED!

302
00:13:24,194 --> 00:13:26,327
SERIOUSLY, I'M ROYALLY FUCKED.

303
00:13:26,370 --> 00:13:28,198
ROXY'S DOWNSTAIRS.
POLICE ESCORT.

304
00:13:28,895 --> 00:13:29,939
COOL.

305
00:13:45,999 --> 00:13:46,913
THOSE ARE MOM'S.

306
00:13:46,956 --> 00:13:48,653
I KNOW.

307
00:13:48,697 --> 00:13:50,612
DO YOU EVER LOOK AT THESE
WHEN SHE'S NOT HOME?

308
00:13:52,919 --> 00:13:55,443
IT'S ALL RIGHT TO BE
CURIOUS, REGGIE.

309
00:13:55,486 --> 00:13:57,445
DEATH IS THE BIGGEST
MYSTERY IN LIFE.

310
00:13:57,488 --> 00:13:59,360
I'D BE WORRIED ABOUT YOU
IF YOU WEREN'T CURIOUS.

311
00:14:04,887 --> 00:14:07,107
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
TO THAT PLACE, REGGIE?

312
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:09,544
THAT PLACE
WHERE GEORGE DIED?MM-MM.

313
00:14:09,587 --> 00:14:12,068
IT'S AN IMPORTANT PLACE
IN HER LIFE.

314
00:14:12,112 --> 00:14:14,636
IT SHOULD BE
AN IMPORTANT PLACE
IN YOURS, TOO.

315
00:14:17,552 --> 00:14:19,336
I KNOW.

316
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:21,904
WE HAVE TO FIND
THE THINGS AND THE PLACES

317
00:14:22,992 --> 00:14:24,037
THAT KEEP GEORGE ALIVE.

318
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,560
THEY'RE EVERYWHERE.

319
00:14:25,603 --> 00:14:27,344
HER--HER SPIRIT...

320
00:14:29,172 --> 00:14:30,870
IT'S ALL AROUND US.

321
00:14:35,483 --> 00:14:38,312
SOMETIMES... I HEAR THINGS.

322
00:14:40,749 --> 00:14:42,142
ME, TOO.

323
00:14:45,058 --> 00:14:46,886
ME, TOO.

324
00:14:50,063 --> 00:14:52,195
ARE THESE
ALL OF YOUR COOL TOPS?

325
00:14:52,239 --> 00:14:54,458
SOME OF THEM ARE DIRTY.
YOU WANT TO SEE THOSE?

326
00:14:54,502 --> 00:14:57,505
I LOVED RIDING
IN THE FRONT SEAT
OF THAT POLICE CRUISER.

327
00:14:57,548 --> 00:14:59,289
IT WAS MY FIRST TIME
WITHOUT HANDCUFFS.

328
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:01,335
IT'S A DAY
OF FIRSTS.

329
00:15:01,378 --> 00:15:02,510
UGH!

330
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:05,252
THIS IS CUTE.

331
00:15:05,295 --> 00:15:06,731
IS THIS BLOOD?

332
00:15:07,254 --> 00:15:08,951
NO. BRAIN.

333
00:15:08,995 --> 00:15:11,475
LAST TUESDAY,
THAT GUY WHO TOOK THE
SHOTGUN TO THE FACE.

334
00:15:11,519 --> 00:15:13,521
DAISY SWORE
SHE COULD GET IT OUT.

335
00:15:13,564 --> 00:15:15,175
PROMISES, PROMISES.

336
00:15:15,218 --> 00:15:18,047
I ALSO LOVED THE FACT
YOU WERE IN THE BACK SEAT,
GEORGE.

337
00:15:18,091 --> 00:15:19,353
YOU LOOKED JUST LIKE A PERP.

338
00:15:20,310 --> 00:15:22,269
YOU ARE JUST
SO PISSED OFF

339
00:15:22,312 --> 00:15:24,488
THAT I GOT A ROCK STAR
AND YOU DIDN'T.

340
00:15:24,532 --> 00:15:26,447
YOU JUST WISH
YOU WERE ME, DON'T YOU?

341
00:15:26,490 --> 00:15:27,796
SHE'S A COCKY
LITTLE THING, ISN'T SHE?

342
00:15:27,839 --> 00:15:29,015
I'M NOT COCKY.

343
00:15:29,058 --> 00:15:30,581
I'M JUST COOLER
THAN YOU ARE.

344
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:32,540
[MIMICKING MASON]
I GOT A ROCK'N'ROLL REAP.

345
00:15:32,583 --> 00:15:33,671
UP YOURS.

346
00:15:33,715 --> 00:15:35,021
THERE'S NOTHING
TO WEAR TO IT.

347
00:15:35,064 --> 00:15:37,762
MY ONLY V.I.P. REAP
WAS CHARLTON HESTON.

348
00:15:37,806 --> 00:15:39,155
HE ISN'T DEAD.

349
00:15:39,199 --> 00:15:40,504
YEAH, BUT ISN'T HE REALLY?

350
00:15:40,548 --> 00:15:42,158
DID RUBE GET A LOT
OF BIG REAPS?

351
00:15:42,202 --> 00:15:43,551
I BET HE HAS.

352
00:15:43,594 --> 00:15:45,292
RUBE IS SO FUCKING OLD,
HE REAPED JESUS.

353
00:15:46,032 --> 00:15:47,294
COME ON, GUYS,

354
00:15:47,337 --> 00:15:48,817
I DON'T SEE WHAT THESE
CLOTHES HAVE GOT TO DO

355
00:15:48,860 --> 00:15:51,037
WITH GETTING TICKETS
TO THE FUCKING ROCK CONCERT.

356
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,255
GEORGE IS A GIRL.

357
00:15:52,299 --> 00:15:54,301
LOOKING GOOD <i>
IS</i>HER TICKET.

358
00:15:54,344 --> 00:15:56,868
YOU HAVE A POLICE BADGE
AND A BLOODY GUN!

359
00:15:56,912 --> 00:15:59,088
AND GEORGE
IS YOUNG AND CUTE.

360
00:16:00,263 --> 00:16:01,830
ARE THESE
ALL YOUR TOPS?

361
00:16:01,873 --> 00:16:04,006
HEY, A DEAD GIRL
HAS GOT TO MAKE DO
WITH VERY LITTLE.

362
00:16:04,050 --> 00:16:06,704
I NEED SOMETHING RACY
AND CLINGY.

363
00:16:06,748 --> 00:16:08,010
YOU STILL
GOT THAT $500?

364
00:16:08,054 --> 00:16:09,403
MOST OF IT.

365
00:16:09,446 --> 00:16:10,795
OOH, ARE WE GOING
TO GO SCALPING?

366
00:16:10,839 --> 00:16:12,145
SHOPPING.

367
00:16:12,188 --> 00:16:13,842
AND YOU'RE
ON YOUR OWN.WHAT?

368
00:16:13,885 --> 00:16:15,278
I DON'T LIKE
YOUR FUCKING ATTITUDE.

369
00:16:15,322 --> 00:16:16,540
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

370
00:16:16,584 --> 00:16:17,672
YOU'RE JOKING!
WHAT?

371
00:16:18,716 --> 00:16:20,457
NO, BUT--
WELL, I'M JUST--

372
00:16:20,501 --> 00:16:22,372
DO YOU TWO THINK
I REALLY NEED YOU

373
00:16:22,416 --> 00:16:24,896
TO GET INTO
A ROCK'N'ROLL ESTABLISHMENT?

374
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:26,550
NO, I DON'T.

375
00:16:26,594 --> 00:16:28,596
I WAS BORN IN
A ROCK'N'ROLL ESTABLISHMENT.

376
00:16:29,858 --> 00:16:31,251
I ACTUALLY WAS.

377
00:16:31,294 --> 00:16:32,643
BEHIND THE AMPS, BACKSTAGE.

378
00:16:32,687 --> 00:16:33,775
[CAR ENGINE STARTING]

379
00:16:33,818 --> 00:16:34,863
ROXY?

380
00:16:34,906 --> 00:16:36,256
[CAR DRIVES AWAY]

381
00:16:38,127 --> 00:16:40,042
I'M SO VICIOUSLY FUCKED.

382
00:16:42,784 --> 00:16:44,264
[RIBBIT]

383
00:16:52,141 --> 00:16:53,403
[KNOCKING]

384
00:16:54,970 --> 00:16:56,058
FATHER MATTHIAS?

385
00:16:57,059 --> 00:16:58,104
CONFESSION IS CLOSED.

386
00:16:58,843 --> 00:17:00,410
I KNOW, I JUST...

387
00:17:01,977 --> 00:17:03,718
WELL, IT'S OCCUPIED ANYWAY.

388
00:17:03,761 --> 00:17:05,328
A BOY AND A GIRL ARE ACTUALLY

389
00:17:05,372 --> 00:17:07,200
DESECRATING
THE CONFESSIONAL.

390
00:17:09,419 --> 00:17:11,943
THEY ARE FRUITFUL
AND MULTIPLYING...

391
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:16,948
ARE YOU DRUNK,
FATHER?

392
00:17:16,992 --> 00:17:19,516
I'M SORRY. I'M NOT BEING
A VERY GOOD PRIEST.

393
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:21,083
NO, YOU CERTAINLY AREN'T.

394
00:17:21,997 --> 00:17:23,738
I KNOW YOU.

395
00:17:23,781 --> 00:17:25,957
WERE YOU HERE FOR CONFESSION
A COUPLE OF WEEKS AGO?

396
00:17:26,915 --> 00:17:28,438
I WAS.

397
00:17:28,482 --> 00:17:31,615
WERE YOU THE ONE
WHO STOLE A CROSS
FROM A DEAD WOMAN?

398
00:17:31,659 --> 00:17:33,530
WELL, IF YOU WANT
TO PUT IT THAT WAY, FINE.

399
00:17:44,715 --> 00:17:46,065
IT'S VERY BEAUTIFUL.

400
00:17:46,108 --> 00:17:46,935
THANK YOU.

401
00:17:49,503 --> 00:17:50,504
SO ARE YOU.

402
00:17:51,157 --> 00:17:52,245
FATHER...

403
00:17:53,115 --> 00:17:54,595
TSK, TSK.

404
00:17:54,638 --> 00:17:56,466
WELL, I'VE DONE
THE DRINKING.

405
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:58,338
AND THE COVETING,
THAT'S A GIVEN.

406
00:17:58,381 --> 00:17:59,904
BUT THAT'S WHERE I STOP.

407
00:18:03,299 --> 00:18:04,213
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

408
00:18:05,171 --> 00:18:07,042
DAISY ADAIR.

409
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,305
MY PARISH IS POOR.

410
00:18:09,349 --> 00:18:13,483
I'VE SPENT A LIFETIME
TRYING TO BRING HOPE
TO THE HOPELESS,

411
00:18:13,527 --> 00:18:16,095
CONVINCING THEM
THAT THERE'S SOME
GREAT REWARD AHEAD.

412
00:18:17,444 --> 00:18:19,924
I WORRY ABOUT
THE HEARTS OF MEN, DAISY.

413
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:21,883
SO DO I.

414
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,801
WOULD YOU LIKE TO KNOW

415
00:18:26,844 --> 00:18:28,846
THE SECRETS OF THE UNIVERSE,
DAISY?

416
00:18:37,464 --> 00:18:38,508
WE ARE BORN.

417
00:18:40,249 --> 00:18:41,424
WE DIE.

418
00:18:42,947 --> 00:18:44,035
WE ROT.

419
00:18:44,079 --> 00:18:46,255
[LAUGHING]

420
00:18:51,565 --> 00:18:53,436
IT'S ALL ONE BIG
COSMIC JOKE!

421
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,091
[THUD]

422
00:19:20,811 --> 00:19:21,856
OH, MY LORD...

423
00:19:34,477 --> 00:19:36,784
I'M WITH THE BAND,
MATE. CHEERS.

424
00:19:36,827 --> 00:19:39,221
UH, EXCUSE ME, HELLO.
I'M WITH THE BAND.

425
00:19:39,265 --> 00:19:40,353
WHY DON'T YOU
UNDERSTAND ME?

426
00:19:40,396 --> 00:19:43,225
I'M... WITH...
THE... BAND.

427
00:19:43,269 --> 00:19:44,618
WHAT DO YOU THINK
KYLE'S GOING TO SAY

428
00:19:44,661 --> 00:19:46,576
WHEN HE SAYS, "WHERE'S
MY BLOODY GUITAR?"

429
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:49,231
AND I SAY, "THE FAT
BLOODY SECURITY PERSON

430
00:19:49,275 --> 00:19:51,233
HELD ME UP AT THE GATE"?

431
00:19:51,277 --> 00:19:53,409
ALL RIGHT.
I'M FRIENDS WITH THE DRUMMER.

432
00:19:53,453 --> 00:19:55,237
WHAT'S
THE DRUMMER'S NAME?

433
00:19:55,281 --> 00:19:57,196
I CALL HIM BY HIS NICKNAME,
YOU KNOW, STICKS.

434
00:19:57,239 --> 00:19:58,284
HIT THE ROAD, JACK.

435
00:19:58,327 --> 00:20:00,024
ROXY, THANK GOD, MAN.

436
00:20:00,068 --> 00:20:01,722
FUCKING--YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'VE BEEN THROUGH HERE.

437
00:20:01,765 --> 00:20:03,376
I MEAN, IN THE GOOD OLD DAYS,
YOU USED TO BE ABLE TO JUST--

438
00:20:03,419 --> 00:20:04,942
SIR, STEP ASIDE.

439
00:20:04,986 --> 00:20:06,292
WHAT?

440
00:20:06,335 --> 00:20:07,771
SIR, DON'T LET ME
HAVE TO ASK YOU AGAIN.

441
00:20:07,815 --> 00:20:09,077
STEP ASIDE.

442
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,818
DON'T PULL THIS
ON ME, ROXY.

443
00:20:10,861 --> 00:20:12,254
DON'T--NO, DON'T GET
YOUR LITTLE FRIEND

444
00:20:12,298 --> 00:20:13,777
TO COME OVER AND
ARREST ME OR ANYTHING,

445
00:20:13,821 --> 00:20:15,214
BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO--ROXY!

446
00:20:15,257 --> 00:20:16,432
YOU HAVE NOT HEARD
THE LAST OF THIS!

447
00:20:16,476 --> 00:20:17,999
DON'T I KNOW IT.

448
00:20:22,569 --> 00:20:23,657
SHE'S WITH THE BAND.

449
00:20:25,702 --> 00:20:27,313
LOOK, SHE'S PRETENDING
NOT TO KNOW ME!

450
00:20:27,356 --> 00:20:29,010
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN,
KID.

451
00:20:29,053 --> 00:20:30,490
DON'T FUCK THIS UP.

452
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:33,232
ROXY, YOU'RE A BUGGER.

453
00:20:33,275 --> 00:20:35,582
<i>YOU KNOW THAT DREAM WHERE
YOU'RE SITTING IN CLASS,</i>

454
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:37,671
<i>AND ALL OF A SUDDEN
YOU REALIZE YOU'RE NAKED?</i>

455
00:20:37,714 --> 00:20:38,889
<i>WELL, I NEVER HAD THAT DREAM.</i>

456
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:43,720
[GROUPIES LAUGHING]

457
00:20:43,764 --> 00:20:44,939
<i>UNTIL NOW.</i>

458
00:20:47,681 --> 00:20:49,857
HEY, DON, GET SOMEONE TO CLEAR
THE FUCKING STEP, HEY?

459
00:20:50,858 --> 00:20:52,294
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

460
00:20:52,338 --> 00:20:53,556
SOMEONE'S GOING TO DIE
AROUND HERE.

461
00:20:54,514 --> 00:20:55,732
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

462
00:20:56,472 --> 00:20:58,344
HEY, I'M JEANNIE,

463
00:20:58,387 --> 00:20:59,954
AND I'M GOING
TO GET YOU A DRINK.

464
00:20:59,997 --> 00:21:01,521
I'M GEORGE,

465
00:21:01,564 --> 00:21:02,870
AND I'M NOT
GOING TO ARGUE.

466
00:21:02,913 --> 00:21:04,872
[CHUCKLES]

467
00:21:04,915 --> 00:21:06,961
SO I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
AROUND HERE BEFORE.

468
00:21:07,004 --> 00:21:08,310
I'M WITH THE NETWORK.

469
00:21:08,354 --> 00:21:10,007
OH. COOL.

470
00:21:10,051 --> 00:21:11,357
WHAT DO YOU DO?

471
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,359
<i>OKAY, YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE,</i>

472
00:21:13,402 --> 00:21:15,404
<i>BUT HAVE NO RESPONSIBILITIES.</i>

473
00:21:15,448 --> 00:21:17,188
I'M AN... INTERN.

474
00:21:18,102 --> 00:21:19,452
NICE.

